#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-ubuntu.adoc:54
msgid "This issue happens with self-installed versions of {ubuntu}.  If the default user has been granted administrative privileges during installation time, a password is required to perform privilege escalation using [command]``sudo``.  With cloud instances this does not happen because [command]``cloud-init`` automatically creates a file under [path]``/etc/sudoers.d`` and grants privilege escalation through [command]``sudo`` without the need for a password."
